** In the Terraform state, define a network security group rule that restricts outbound traffic from the application servers to only known allowed service URLs (`https://api.company.com/*`). Use the `aws_security_group` resource with `ingress` and `egress` rules:  
```hcl
resource "aws_security_group" "app_sg" {
  name = "app-sg"
  description = "Restrict outbound SSRF"
  ingress { cidr_blocks = ["10.0.0.0/16"] }
  egress  {
    cidr_blocks = ["10.0.0.0/16"]
    description = "Allow only internal APIs"
    prefix_list_ids = ["pl-123456"] // For the API service
  }
}
```
Additionally, enable the `aws_lb_listener_rule` to block internal IP ranges. Mitigation also involves validating and sanitizing all URLs in the file‑upload logic. The 2024 “UnleashedUpload” breach of an e‑commerce platform leveraged an SSRF in a third‑party image optimizer.  

